You can run the following piece of codes successfully in these 3 SAS programming environments:
 BASE SAS  Enterprise Guide: create a new “File-New-Program”  SAS Data Integration Studio: create a new “Tool-Code Editor”    %let species=&ldquo;Setosa&rdquo; &ldquo;Versicolor&rdquo;;
data a; &#160;&#160;&#160; set sashelp.iris; &#160;&#160;&#160; where species in (&amp;species); run; 

 Then create a Transformation in SAS Data Integration Studio (DIS for short; I use version 4.
